      "dimension": "cross_module_architecture",
      "identifier": "inconsistent_contract_definition_convention",
      "summary": "Contract declarations use inconsistent mutability and export conventions across modules, weakening boundary integrity.",
      "related_files": [
        "goseg/protocol/contracts/protocol_contracts.go",
        "goseg/protocol/contracts/startram_contracts.go"
      ],
      "evidence": [
        "`protocol_contracts.go` anchors IDs/actions/compatibility in typed constants and maps exports to those constants.",
        "`startram_contracts.go` keeps key contract values in package vars (`apiConnectionErrorMessage`, `startramApiConnectionErrorContract`) and exports `APIConnectionError` as a mutable var derived from another var at init-time.",
        "No shared rule enforces one declaration style, so future modules can diverge further and increase coupling to init-time state."
      ],
      "suggestion": "Define and enforce a single contract declaration convention (prefer immutable typed constants for IDs/metadata, with generated or helper-based entry construction), then normalize both files to that convention.",
